abstract: “It’s not going to be just one woman running,” said Kirsten Gillibrand, one of three senators who positioned themselves this week as potential presidential candidates in 2020.
snippet: “It’s not going to be just one woman running,” said Kirsten Gillibrand, one of three senators who positioned themselves this week as potential presidential candidates in 2020.
lead_paragraph: GREENVILLE, S.C. — Three prominent female Democrats all but openly began running for president this week, taking their most active steps yet to challenge President Trump and claim leadership of a movement of moderate and liberal women that has come to define their party during the 2018 elections.

abstract: The United Nations ambassador, who has announced she will resign at year’s end, tried her hand at humor as guest speaker.
snippet: The United Nations ambassador, who has announced she will resign at year’s end, tried her hand at humor as guest speaker.
lead_paragraph: Nikki R. Haley joked about President Trump’s braggadocio in his United Nations speech last month. Once, she said, he asked if she belonged to the same Native American tribe as Senator Elizabeth Warren. And as a member of Mr. Trump’s cabinet, she added, “It is a thrill to be out to dinner without being harassed.”

abstract: If the president’s unpopularity leads to Democrats taking back the House, New York stands to play a larger role in Washington than it has in decades.
snippet: If the president’s unpopularity leads to Democrats taking back the House, New York stands to play a larger role in Washington than it has in decades.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump may well be one of the few New York leaders liked by the heartland of America. Yet his growing unpopularity elsewhere may not only fuel a Democratic resurgence in November — it may be the very thing that propels more New Yorkers into power.

headline_main: Will Trump Make New York Democrats the New Lords of Capitol Hill?
headline_print_headline: After Midterms, a Power Boost for New York Democrats?

abstract: The possible Democratic front-runner plays Trump’s game — and loses.
snippet: The possible Democratic front-runner plays Trump’s game — and loses.
lead_paragraph: A lot of smart people believe that Elizabeth Warren, the senator from Massachusetts, is the front-runner for the Democratic nomination in 2020. A recent New York magazine profile by Jonathan Chait claimed that she’s winning the invisible primary — building campaign networks, rolling out policy proposals, wooing insiders, intimidating rivals.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: C.E.O.s Are America’s New Diplomats

abstract: The media was happy to sing his praises in the spring, when the crown prince met with Hollywood stars and Silicon Valley titans. Then came the Jamal Khashoggi story.
snippet: The media was happy to sing his praises in the spring, when the crown prince met with Hollywood stars and Silicon Valley titans. Then came the Jamal Khashoggi story.
lead_paragraph: Just six months ago, American media outlets presented a sunny-side-up portrait of Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman of Saudi Arabia as he made a good-will tour of New York, Hollywood and Silicon Valley.

abstract: New York City’s plan to close Rikers Island calls for putting 1,500 inmate beds in the building that houses the Manhattan Marriage Bureau — and moving the weddings out.
snippet: New York City’s plan to close Rikers Island calls for putting 1,500 inmate beds in the building that houses the Manhattan Marriage Bureau — and moving the weddings out.
lead_paragraph: Carlos Sanchez was talking about love and loss: his love for Jennifer Avila and for the place where they were married in 2009. The loss will come if the city turns that place into a jail, as it plans to.

abstract: A conference for big investors started last year by Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman has become a symbol of the West’s deepening disillusionment with him after the disappearance of a Saudi journalist.
snippet: A conference for big investors started last year by Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman has become a symbol of the West’s deepening disillusionment with him after the disappearance of a Saudi journalist.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The participants nicknamed it “Davos in the Desert,” which captures the lofty ambitions of the annual investor conference scheduled to convene in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, this month.
